Even though I am a fan of Pewds, I didn't buy this game for that reason.
I bought it mainly because it was cheap & I loved the general style of the game.

Pros;
:: The visual style is highly appealing {reminded me of the scott pilgrim game - similar soundtrack too, the look also reminded me of a few other side scrollers like mario & the TMNT game back in the 80/90's}
:: It's an extra thing for fans of pewdiepie / cinnamontoastken / jacksepticeye / cutiepiemarzia / markiplier / maya & edgar to enjoy
:: There's a decent selection of characters & upgrades to unlock
:: The game goes from pretty easy to rediculously challenging - so atleast those who want a challenge can have it
:: Even though the first play through of the game can be completed within a few hours, there is the option to go back & re-do levels at higher difficulties, allowing for countless hours of fun {or frustration}

Cons;
:: Even though the coin system is great, it seems to take an age to collect enough coins to spend on unlocking upgrades & new characters.
:: The voice acting at times is too forced & irritating {I honestly don't know if dull sarcasm was the approach they were going for} so I found myself skipping the dialog scenes or turning down the volume as it was a bit cringe worthy.
:: Depending on the level of difficulty you choose to play on - it can be insanely short gameplay wise for the first run through {I took less than 4 hours to fully complete on easy}
:: The rewards that you get in the game are a bit lacking.  Personally I would prefer something more than just collecting patches, like getting unlockable customisations for characters.


The creators have decided to take a selection of classic & iconic game features & merged them into this cute side scrolling adventure game.  It's nostalgic, it's a good time waster & for the money it's a great wee game to have in your library.

In saying that, there's still a lot more potential for the game to grow.  Although my review may seem harsh considering the team worked hard to create what they have & the game was released not too long ago.
I'm hoping now that they can expand on the game adding extra features - like maybe a time trial, allowing players to earn extra items by competing against thousands of other bros worldwide for the best time.  As I said earlier, more items for you to unlock beside patches.  Perhaps even bringing in new characters in the future.
